 The Chief of Air Staff, Air Marshal Sadique Abubakar, on Saturday implored Nigerian Air Force (NAF) personnel to maintain good civil-military relations in order not to put the Force in disrepute. Abubakar made the call during the inauguration of renovated four blocks of one-bedroom flat at the second officers’ transit quarters at NAF base in Kaduna. “I implore all of you to maintain good civil-military relations in order not to put the Service in disrepute, ” Abubakar said. Continue reading NAF chief tasks personnel on civil/military relations at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard